column5: Man that sure was a nice day today. I had to haul equipment out of Milton all day and wished i could have spent the day instead out on the boat fishing . I  wondered  how many people did get out and had a good day of fishing ?

i bet ya were dieing to get your new sonar hooked up and workin. BTW i picked one up too.I'm a sucker for a sale. It was windy and cold here today. I raked up 21 huge bags of leaves from my maple trees.

I  got home just a while ago from my day of work that was'nt suppose to not happen during my week ends off ........ but it did help out a friend . So here i am eatting supper , answering my messages , and returning phone call and wanting to go chech the wind and weather forcast for tomorrow to see if i could get out at least for one more day . It would be nice to try out the new finder alright and bring home another catch of fish , maybe even get pb ........... lol.
It was a nice day to get skunked...  Tried for rainbows on lake O tribs today...  Zack got 1 and I got skunked...  I got a tan tho...  We'll make it up tomorrow on the Larry...
I hear ya Mike , i wish you luck for tomorrow .
Hopefully I get a pic this time...  Last weekend I got a 9.6lb walleye and buddy took the pic with his finger over the lense...  I was so mad!!!!!!
That would hurt alright ......... no pic .

Nice day indeed. I was making sure that a bunch of diesel doesn't reach White River.... I'm glad it didn't, but I'd still rather be fishing the river. The pike and walleye are safe for now.  ..oh, and I have to drive by all them nice steelhead rivers between Marathon and Thunder Bay with no fishing rod...woe is me.  As a consolation, I get to watch the hockey game from the comfort of a Jacuzzi tub. Woe is me
You do know that if i hadda been there, you would have your pic. But where was i????Oh Ya I was here DEAMING OF FISHING!!!!
Some people know how to live alright ......
After raking leaves, I went out for a hike and some pond fishing for crappie. Only managed 4 but it was a great day to be outside regardless!
